itemDescription: fireman and stoker who survived the sinking of the Titanic

wikipedia_page.main: Arthur John Priest (31 August 1887 – 11 February 1937) was an English fireman and stoker who was notable for surviving five ship sinkings including the RMS Titanic, HMHS Asturias, the RMS Alcantara, HMHS Britannic and the SS Donegal. Due to these incidents, Priest gained the moniker "the unsinkable stoker".
